# Landing page UX (48-hour Google profile DIY kit)

**Voice:** Plain English for local business owners; no dev jargon (no async, sprint, GBP, intake, deliverable, pre-qual).

## Conversion checklist

Before shipping changes to `index.html`, `styles.css`, or `app.js`, confirm:

1. **Hero** — Outcome headline (≤ 20 words), one-line proof, price anchor ($129.99 / **48 hours**), **~5 min** customer time after pay, primary CTA above fold.
2. **Trust** — Hero bullets (≤ 12 words each): DIY / no login, 48h delivery, 5 business-day refund.
3. **Fit** — Compact for / not-for blocks; no long paragraphs.
4. **Deliverables** — Scannable numbered or icon list; lead with brochure + report outcome (customer applies changes).
5. **Proof** — Sample report with before/after (fictional business); optional form preview; no fake testimonials.
6. **Flow** — “After you pay”: Pay → Short form (~5 min) → Brochure + report in **48 hours**.
7. **CTA** — $129.99 + 3 confirm checkboxes gate Stripe; set **`data-stripe-url`** on **`#pay-cta`** to a `https://buy.stripe.com/…` Payment Link before go-live (see **`docs/setup-what-you-need.md`**).
8. **Objections** — FAQ capped at **5** items (include “Why 48 hours?”); footer disclaimer one line.
9. **Mobile** — Sticky bottom bar: price + gated CTA when pre-qual passes; safe-area padding.

## Copy limits

| Element | Limit |
|---------|--------|
| Hero headline | ≤ 20 words |
| Trust / fit bullets | ≤ 12 words each |
| Section intros | 1–2 sentences |
| FAQ answers | 1 sentence preferred |

Prefer verbs and outcomes over feature lists. No ranking or call-volume guarantees.

## Visual system

- **Font**: DM Sans (or equivalent); display scale for `h1`, muted body (`--ink-muted`).
- **Accents**: Flip7 palette from `docs/flip7-card-game-DESIGN.md` — teal, coral, gold as borders/CTAs only; avoid playful/game UI.
- **Surface**: Subtle mesh/gradient background, 12–16px radius, refined shadows, visible `:focus-visible` states.
- **Motion**: Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; no decorative loops on the landing page.

## Reference URLs

Add competitor/reference URLs when provided. Until then, pattern-match high-converting service landings (clear hero, single CTA rhythm, social proof strip, objection FAQ) — e.g. Stripe payment pages, Linear-style SaaS heroes — without copying brand assets.

## Ship gate: screenshot review

**Do not ship visual changes** without reviewing a local screenshot at mobile (~390px) and desktop widths:

1. Run preview on port **5173** (`start5173.bat`) or **8080**.
2. Capture hero, trust strip, checkout (disabled + enabled CTA), sticky bar, and doc preview open state.
3. Fix contrast, alignment, and overflow before commit.

## Do not break

- **`data-stripe-url`** on **`#pay-cta`** (Payment Link) and 3 `name="prequal"` checkboxes.
- `app.js` gate: both `#pay-cta` and `#pay-cta-sticky` stay disabled until all boxes are checked **and** `data-stripe-url` is a `https://buy.stripe.com/…` URL.
